{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 1 presents a schematic overview of our proposed methodology.",
    "Detailed implementation and source code for the system are available on GitHub foot_3.",
    "We evaluated traditional ML models, including Logistic Regression, Support Vector Machines (SVM), Random Forest (RF), Naïve Bayes (NB), Decision Trees (DT), Kernel SVM, and Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD), for product review classification.",
    "Textual data was transformed into high-dimensional vectors using TF-IDF (Takenobu, 1994) and CountVectorizer, with TF-IDF limited to 1000 features for optimal performance.",
    "Logistic regression used a maximum of 1000 iterations."
  ]
}